photos.description:
We cordially invite you to the IRIA 2023 i.e 75th ANNUAL CONFERENCE Hosted by IRIA at Amritsar (Punjab) from 2nd February to 5th February 2023.

IRIA Annual Conference is the biggest Medical Event in the field of radiology and medical imaging where leading medical professionals, doctors, researchers, and scientists participate and collaborate.

Phantom Healthcare is one of the leading exhibitors at this conference. Please visit us at our Stall No. G-6 at the Venue: Guru Nanak Dev University, Amritsar.

75th Annual conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association [IRIA] to be hosted by the Punjab State Chapter of IRIA along with State Chapters of Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Ladakh & Chandigarh as Co-Host, in the holy city of Amritsar from 2nd to 5th February 2023 at Guru Nanak Dev University. We extend a warm invitation to you all to attend this Academic, Cultural, Spiritual, Gastronomical & Sports Fiesta.

photos.title: Timeline photos
photos.description:
National Science Day is celebrated in India every year on 28 February to mark the discovery of the Raman Effect by Indian physicist Sir C.V. Raman on February 28, 1928. The Raman effect refers to the scattering of light by molecules, and this discovery earned Raman the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1930.

The celebration of National Science Day is an important event for India as it encourages the youth of the country to take interest in science and technology and to promote scientific research and development in the country.

World Brain Tumor Day is celebrated every year on the 8th of June to make people aware of growing brain tumours globally and educate them on preventive measures.

Symptoms of a brain tumour depend on the location and size of the tumour. Some tumours directly damage the brain tissues and some tumours pressure the surrounding parts. It's most common to have headaches often. Along with this if you are feeling some other symptoms for a long time then you should consult a doctor.

World Brain Tumor Day 2024

World Brain Tumor Day is celebrated every year on the 8th of June to make people aware of growing brain tumours globally and educate them on preventive measures.

Symptoms of a brain tumour depend on the location and size of the tumour. Some tumours directly damage the brain tissues and some tumours pressure the surrounding parts. It's most common to have headaches often. Along with this if you are feeling some other symptoms for a long time then you should consult a doctor.

âHeadache or pressure which is high in the morning.
âBeing nauseous or vomiting often.
âEye problems, such as blurred appearance or double vision.
âNot functioning properly of one arm or one leg.
âDifficulty in physical-mental balance.
âKeep feeling so tired.
âDetect tumours by MRI and CT scan

We are thrilled to invite you to the 23rd Asian Oceanian Congress of Radiology (AOCR 2025) and the 77th Annual Conference of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA 2025), scheduled to take place from January 23 to 26, 2025, at the Chennai Trade Centre, Nandambakkam, Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India.

Theme: "Clinical Radiology Decoded â See like a Surgeon: Think Like a Physician"

Organizers: Hosted by the Tamil Nadu & Pondicherry Chapter of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA) and the Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology (AOSR).

Phantom Healthcare is proud to be one of the leading exhibitors at this prestigious event. Having participated in the IRIA Annual Conference for many years, we remain committed to supporting the growth of the radiology community. Join us at our stall to explore the latest in refurbished medical imaging equipment, including MRI, CT, PET-CT, Bone Densitometer DEXA, Gamma Camera SPECT, CATH lab machines, and more.

Key Highlights:

Scientific Sessions: Engage with leading experts through interactive lectures and hands-on workshops.
Networking Opportunities: Connect with professionals and industry leaders from around the world.
Exhibition: Discover cutting-edge technologies in medical imaging and radiology.
Registration Details:

We look forward to seeing you in Chennai for an enriching and memorable experience!

Organizers: Hosted by the Tamil Nadu & Pondicherry Chapter of the Indian Radiological & Imaging Association (IRIA) and the Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology (AOSR).

About IRIA & AOSR:
IRIA (Indian Radiological & Imaging Association), founded in 1951, is India's leading professional body dedicated to the growth and development of radiology and medical imaging. The association brings together radiologists, radiographers, and imaging professionals to promote research, education, and best practices in the field of radiology. With a strong network of members, IRIA organizes various scientific conferences, workshops, and training programs, making it a significant player in shaping the future of radiology in India.

AOSR (Asian Oceanian Society of Radiology), established in 1981, is an international organization that serves as a collaborative platform for radiology professionals across the Asia-Pacific region. AOSR aims to promote radiology practices, research, and education, and to provide opportunities for networking and knowledge exchange among professionals. Its flagship event, the Asian Oceanian Congress of Radiology (AOCR), gathers experts from around the world to discuss the latest innovations and developments in radiology.

National Science Day is celebrated in India every year on 28 February to mark the discovery of the Raman Effect by Indian physicist Sir C.V. Raman on February 28, 1928. The Raman effect refers to the scattering of light by molecules, and this discovery earned Raman the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1930.

The celebration of National Science Day is an important event for India as it encourages the country's youth to take an interest in science and technology and promote scientific research and development in the country.
